(458, 60, 'Handmade Sterling Silver \'45 Centre\' Cufflinks'),
(458, 61, 'RCA Music unveiled the 45 RPM record in 1949. The format was an instant hit. The 7\" inch records were cute, portable, inexpensive and colourful. Every music genre of music had its own colour of vinyl and popular releases were on standard black vinyl. Some kids traded hockey cards - we traded 45s. And they even had a \'B side\'! 45\'s gave way to the \"Mix Tape Era\" in the early 1980\'s, but nostalgia for the 45 and the 45 adapter will forever live on in the hearts of music lovers the world over. Remember the 45? These cufflinks are for you!'),
