(508, 61, 'Agate is one of the oldest gemstones in recorded history and is found in many colours in the earth\'s crust. It is a variety of chalcedony, a form of cryptocrystalline quartz, which is made up of crystal structures so fine they cannot be seen even under most magnification. Due to their ancient nature, agates have a great deal of significance as a healing crystal. Agates are typically thought to provide protection against various threats, including nightmares, stress and exhaustion. White agate is thought to offer an especially pure form of protection because of its “pure” colour. This knotted strand of white agate consists of 10 mm round beads, with a 10 mm sterling silver ball clasp and measures approximately 18 inches.'),
(508, 62, 'Agate is one of the oldest gemstones in recorded history and is found in many colours in the earth\'s crust. It is a variety of chalcedony, a form of cryptocrystalline quartz, which is made up of crystal structures so fine they cannot be seen even under most magnification.'),
(508, 63, 'knotted-agate-ball-necklace'),
(508, 85, 'Taxable Goods'),
(509, 60, 'Knotted Barrel Cut Amethyst Beads with 14K White Gold Clasp'),
(509, 61, 'Tamara purchased the amethysts in this strand in Tucson from a gemcutter who travels the world looking for material to cut in interesting ways. These amethysts are from Brazil and have been cut into hexagonal barrels with domed tops and bottoms. Inclusions and variation in colour among the amethysts add interest. The pieces graduate as you get to the centre of the necklace, and vary in length. The pieces are knotted simply with a white gold clasp. The necklace is approximately 18 inches long.'),
(509, 62, 'Tamara purchased the amethysts in this strand in Tucson from a gemcutter who travels the world looking for material to cut in interesting ways. These amethysts are from Brazil and have been cut into hexagonal barrels with domed tops and bottoms. Inclusions and variation in colour among the amethysts add interest. The pieces graduate as you get to the centre of the necklace, and vary in length. The pieces are knotted simply with a white gold clasp. The necklace is approximately 18 inches long.'),
(509, 63, 'knotted-barrel-cut-amethyst-beads-white-gold clasp'),
(509, 85, 'Taxable Goods'),
(510, 60, 'Knotted Chrome Diopside Flat Bead Necklace with Rose Gold and White Gold Clasp'),
(510, 61, 'Chrome diopside was only discovered in 1988, and initially, all of the material came from Eastern Siberia, though recently, deposits have also been discovered in Pakistan. Though it is relatively new, I predict it will be in demand because naturally occurring bright green gemstones are very rare. I bought the materials for this chrome diopside necklace from a Brazilian supplier of mine at the Tucson gem shows, and they are Russian in origin (the beads were cut and tumbled in Brazil. The colour is rich, though included, and the necklace has a ton of presence and sparkle. This necklace measures approximately 18\" and the largest bead is approximately 15 mm x 23 mm.'),
(510, 62, 'Chrome diopside was only discovered in 1988, and initially, all of the material came from Eastern Siberia, though recently, deposits have also been discovered in Pakistan. Though it is relatively new, I predict it will be in demand because naturally occurring bright green gemstones are very rare.'),
(510, 63, 'knotted-chrome-diopside-necklace-with-rose-white-gold-clasp'),
(510, 85, 'Taxable Goods'),
