(39, 36, 0, 9, 'We all have potentially beautiful objects that have been relegated to the bottom of a box or the back of a cupboard. My grandmother had a box of buttons next to the sewing machine when I was growing up but they had long been put away. By incorporating these objects into precious jewellery, the buttons are elevated to a place of honour, placed in a structure where they can be kept safe and venerated. These pieces celebrate the ‘non’-precious and remind us that beauty can sometimes be constructed from odds and ends.'),
