(1337, 61, 0, 340, '<p><em>Award Winning Necklace</em> in the \"Formula\" show at <em>Zilbershmuck Art Jewellery</em>, March 2008.</p>\r\n<p>One of the most common formulas used by goldsmiths is that required to alloy 14K gold.  This pendant deconstructs the alloy to reveal its proportional parts, so that if melted down, the resulting ingot would be 14K gold.  The pendant is exactly 58.5% fine gold by weight (centre disc), 15% fine silver (ring) and 26.5% copper (crown).  The form of the pendant is the ancient alchemical symbol for gold.  For the alchemist, gold represented the perfection of all matter, including perfection of the mind, spirit and soul.</p>'),
