(1610, 61, 0, 441, 'A client came to me after her home had been tragically broken into and she had lost all of their jewellery.  One of the things she was very upset to lose was a pair of vintage sapphire, ruby and yellow gold earrings that she had bought years before in a Paris flea market.  \r\n\r\nShe did have a copy of the appraisal, and was able to describe them in detail, and I was able to reconstruct them from her records.  It was a very special and meaningful project to my client, and I loved the challenge of the reconstruction.'),
