(1792, 61, 0, 505, 'I did my undergraduate studies at Brandeis University and made these for a client who is a fellow alumnus. They are a classy but modern take on the very elaborate Brandeis University crest and I had a ton of fun designing and making them. I especially love the backs.\r\n\r\nBrandeis University opened in 1948 with 107 students and 13 faculty members, and was named for former U.S. Supreme Court Justice Louis Brandeis. The school has grown since then in both size and status, and it\'s motto is \"Truth, Even Unto its Innermost Parts.\" It was a wonderful place to go to school, and I value my continued connection to the university and to fellow alumni in Canada and around the world. '),
