(1797, 61, 0, 507, 'The soft tones of this asymmetrical moonstone necklace are soothing and elegant. \r\n\r\nMoonstone is a gemstone from the feldspar family that is found all over the world. The faceted, cloudy white/cream, pink and grey moonstone in this necklace comes from several different strands of moonstone that Tamara has collected on her travels to Tucson, and was mined and cut in India. \r\n\r\nThe strand is approximately 20 inches long, and the largest bead measures approximately 13 mm x 18 mm x 6 mm. The clasp is a sterling silver spring ring.\r\n'),
