(1812, 61, 0, 512, 'Pink opal is a natural gemstone found in the Andes mountains in Peru. Pink opals are thought to foster inspiration, imagination and creativity, and to symbolize love and kindness. \r\n\r\nThis strand of round 6 mm opal beads is beautifully cut and simply knotted with a 14K white gold ball clasp to create a very elegant alternative to a traditional strand of pearls. \r\n\r\nThis strand is approximately 18 inches long and has a 7 mm white gold ball clasp.'),
